## AI Summary Format — this is important

The `ai_summary` field must be a genuinely useful qualitative assessment, not marketing prose. Be direct. Structure it as:

> Two sentences on the overall fit, including the headline trade-off.
> Example: "Solid AI-infra role at an accelerating Series C with real s-curve potential. Main trade-off is level — this is a Staff IC role versus the candidate's current Director scope, so they'd be trading management breadth for hands-on problem depth."

Then use `take_it_if`, `compromises`, and `blockers` for the structured recommendations (these render as bullets in the UI).

